webHelper_errorMsg()

Description
    string webHelper_errorMsg(string $error)
    Builds an error message with the proper markup for display.

Parameters
    error
        A string value containing the text of the error message.

Return Values
    Returns a string value containing the error message with the appropriate markup.
    
Examples
    <?php
	...
	// Check for duplicates
	if (webHelper_listDupeCheck($engine->cleanPost['MYSQL']['newListItem'],$table,$engine)) {
	    return webHelper_errorMsg("Entry, ".$engine->cleanPost['HTML']['newListItem'].", already in database.");
	}
	...
    ?>

See Also
    webHelper_successMsg()
